Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a #large pot{} of @salt{to taste} water.

Chop the @potatoes{400%grams} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until fork tender, ~{15-20%mins}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the #pot{}, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{to taste} and a splash of @?milk{to taste} or water and mash until smooth.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cut the @cauliflower{1%unit} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Pop the florets onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, sprinkle over the @ground cumin{1%sachet}, and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

Roast until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Roughly chop the @chives{5%grams} (use #scissors{} if easier) and set aside.

Thinly slice the @mushrooms{150%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%units} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%pack}.

Meanwhile, place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the mushrooms and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cook until browned, ~{5-6%mins}.

Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%min}. Add the @harissa paste{1%sachet} and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Add 50ml water (double for 4p), @passata{1%pack}, lentils and @vegetable stock{1%sachet}. Stir to combine then bring to the boil.

Reduce heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%mins}.

> TIP: Add a little water if it's too thick.

Once the cauliflower is cooked, stir it through the sauce, then remove pan from heat.

Taste your filling and season if needed, then transfer to an #oven dish{}.

Top with an even layer of mash mixed with half the chives and sprinkle over the @grated cheese{50%grams}.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{10-15%mins}.

Divide your savoury pie between plates.

Finish with a sprinkling of the remaining chives.